                    {
                        "unit_id": 887,
                        "title": "3 Steps to Use at the Start of Business Meetings",
                        "slug": "3-steps-use-start-business-meetings",
                        "order": 20,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "Q8Xy1W_lS6I",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h5>The 3 steps that will help you kick-off your next business meeting:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5>Proposing an Agenda</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5>State Value to customer</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5>Check for acceptance</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<h5>In this video you will learn about a how to start a meeting on the right footing.</h5>\r\n<h5>After initially welcoming the client and having a cordial social interaction to break the ice, it is good to set a structure for the meeting to get the most out of it.</h5>\r\n<h5><strong>Here are 3 steps that will help you kick-off your next meeting:</strong></h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5><strong>Proposing an Agenda </strong>to guide the meeting</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5><strong>State Value to customer </strong>so that they understand what’s in it for them</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5><strong>Check for acceptance </strong>get a confirmation that you are both aligned</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>An example after following the above tips, you can start a meeting by saying:</h5>\r\n<h5><em>I’d like for the next 5 minutes to understand more about your needs, then explain to you some of the our offerings, that would address your needs so you can have an informed decision about next steps, does that sound good to you? </em></h5>\r\n<h5>These tips would help you structure your next meeting so that you achieve the most out of it.</h5>",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "<h5>T<span id=\"yiv2243609807yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461823491862_39078\">he next time you're in a meeting</span><span id=\"yiv2243609807yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461823491862_39079\">,</span><span id=\"yiv2243609807yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461823491862_39080\">look around</span><span id=\"yiv2243609807yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461823491862_39081\"> and identify the yes-butters, the not-Knowers and the why- notters. Why- notters move the world. Louise Pierson </span></h5>",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5 id=\"yiv2105025622yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461923237067_89175\">You can start a meeting by saying: I’d like for the next 5 minutes to understand more about your needs, then explain to you some of the our offerings, that would address your needs so you can have an informed decision about next steps, does that sound good to you?</h5>",
