                    {
                        "unit_id": 888,
                        "title": "Uncover your Client’s Needs",
                        "slug": "uncover-clients-needs",
                        "order": 30,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "W8VGHyQgCAA",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h5>The two questioning methods to uncover clients’ needs:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5>Open questions</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5>Closed questions</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<h5>In this video you will learn about how to uncover client needs.</h5>\r\n<h5>After opening a meeting and setting an agenda, then next aim is to uncover the client needs. You don’t have time to tell them about all your products, so first understand what their needs are and then you can tell them only about the products or solutions that meet those needs.</h5>\r\n<h5><strong>Use two questioning methods to uncover needs:</strong></h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5><strong>Open questions </strong>that give the client an opportunity to shed light and expand on the question area</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li>\r\n<h5><strong>Closed questions </strong>that force the client to give you a specific answer such as when a decision would be made</h5>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>The aim of the questioning is to uncover the client’s circumstances and needs which would help you in suggesting the best solutions to their requirements.</h5>\r\n<h5>Remember, listening is a much more effective skill than talking when in meetings.</h5>",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "<h5>People don't care how much you know until they know how much you care. Theodore Roosevelt</h5>",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>John sells personal computers to companies. He has many models of computers, so when he goes to his clients and wants to recommend the right model, he needs to understand their needs very well. The common questions that he uses to uncover needs are open questions like, what will the computers be used for? What are the most required features that are needed? and some closed questions like, how many do you need? when will you need them?</h5>",
                            "course-unit-last-related-content": "",
                            "course-unit-customrelated": "",
                            "course-unit-page-show-game": "",
                            "course-unit-page-show-related": "",
                            "course-unit-page-ads": "",
                            "action_plan": "",
